sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1331005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Modified rhlABRI operon genes from Pseudomonas aeruginosa SQ6
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tianyi Huang

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1331003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: RhlI Acyl-homoserine-lactone synthase from P.aeruginosa SQ6
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This sequece encodes RhlI, an acyl-homoserine-lactone synthase required for the synthesis of BHL (N-butanoyl-L-homoserine lactone), and HHL (N-hexanoyl-L-homoserine lactone) autoinducer molecules which bind to RhlR.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jiayi Dong
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It comes from the genomic sequence of P.aeruginosa SQ6.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It includes both the complete coding sequence of RhlI and part of noncoding sequence between RhlR and RhlI gene.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1331002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: RhlR regulatory protein from P. aeruginosa SQ6
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Coding a transcription regulator RhlR. RhlR is necessary for transcriptional activation of the rhlAB genes encoding the rhamnosyltransferase. It also functions as a transcriptional activator of elastase structural gene (lasB). RhlR binds to autoinducer molecules BHL (N-butanoyl-L-homoserine lactone), and HHL (N-hexanoyl-L-homoserine lactone). This part includes the noncoding sequence of RhlR.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jiayi Dong
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: It comes from the genomic sequence of Pseudomonas aeruginosa SQ6.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It includes both the complete coding sequence and part of noncoding sequence of RhlR.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1331004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Modified rhlB coding sequence from Pseudomonas aeruginosa SQ6
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: RhlB together with RhlA encodes Rhamnosyltransferase I for mono-rahmnolipids biosynthesis in Pseudomonas aeruginosa. This part includes bp upstream noncoding gene and bp downstreanm gene of RhlB. Two mutations have been done to remove the PstI restriction sites contained in the coding sequence, which won't change the amino acid sequence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tianyi Huang
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Two mutations have been done to remove the PstI restriction sites contained in the coding sequence, which won't change the amino acid sequence.
